I tried to say that <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br /><br />To be VERY CLEAR: DO NOT USE a 3V ROM IN a 5V SYSTEM WITHOUT ADDING VOLTAGE SHIFTING.<br /><br />The easiest options are GTL FET clamps (such as the GTL2008) or voltage buffers such as the 74ALVC16245.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3512">lidnariq</a> — Sun Jan 11, 2015 9:07 pm</p><hr />
