<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12240&amp;p=139119#p139119"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">lidnariq wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />3V parallel EEPROMs are quite affordable (digikey mentions a 2MiB one for $1.50/1), and come in capacities up to 256MiB ($9/1).<br /><br />You will have to add voltage shifting (e.g. 74'16245) and a voltage regulator, but 3.3V logic is compatible with 5V TTL signalling as used in older consoles.<br /></div><br /><br />If you are using 3.3V logic in a 5V system at least put some low resistance (~100 ohm) resistors on relevant lines or do level shifting for data as well.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5314">mikejmoffitt</a> — Sun Jan 11, 2015 8:47 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
