<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Looking to adapt some boards I have. Questions.]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12240&amp;p=139111#p139111"><![CDATA[
3V parallel EEPROMs are quite affordable (digikey mentions a 2MiB one for $1.50/1), and come in capacities up to 256MiB ($9/1).<br /><br />You will have to add voltage shifting (e.g. 74'16245) and a voltage regulator, but 3.3V logic is compatible with 5V TTL signalling as used in older consoles.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3512">lidnariq</a> — Sun Jan 11, 2015 6:12 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
